nodes.examples:
Format Examples


dd-MM-yy : 31-01-12
dd-MM-yyyy : 31-01-2012
MM-dd-yyyy : 01-31-2012
yyyy-MM-dd : 2012-01-31
yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss : 2012-01-31 23:59:59

yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSSZ : 2012-01-31 23:59:59.999+0100

nodes.name: Clean user id and calculate age
nodes.description: This node runs the given SQL on the incoming DataFrame

fields.name: storageLevel
fields.title: Output Storage Level
fields.description: Storage Level of the Output Datasets of this Node

fields.name: tempTable
fields.title: Temp Table
fields.description: Temp Table Name to be used

fields.name: sql
fields.value:
select concat('{', SWID , '}') as swid, 
CAST(datediff(from_unixtime(unix_timestamp()),
 from_unixtime(unix_timestamp(BIRTH_DT, 'dd-MMM-yy'))) / 365 AS INT) age,
GENDER_CD as gender_cd from temp_users
fields.title: SQL
fields.description: SQL to be run

nodes.name: Join with User Data
nodes.description: This node registers the incoming DataFrames as temporary tables and executes the SQL provided

fields.name: storageLevel
fields.title: Output Storage Level
fields.description: Storage Level of the Output Datasets of this Node

fields.name: tempTables
fields.title: Temp Table Names
fields.description: Temp Table Name to be used

fields.name: sql
fields.value:
select ts ,ip ,url ,city ,country ,state ,logdate, 
category, correct_age as age, gender_cd from omniture_product op FULL JOIN users u 
ON(op.swid=u.swid)
fields.title: SQL
fields.description: SQL to be run

nodes.description: Allows capturing Notes on the Workflow

fields.name: storageLevel
fields.title: Output Storage Level
fields.description: Storage Level of the Output Datasets of this Node

fields.name: comment
fields.value:
Omniture Clickstream Data Analysis


This workflow reads in the Omniture clickstream data, product and users data.


It cleans and joins them to get the denormalized clean dataset.


It then performs the following analysis:


  • Finds number of users by state and displays them on a map.
  • Finds number of users by age and displays them on a graph.
fields.title: Comment
fields.description: Comments for the Workflow
